<TITLE> Man held at ZIA with Tk 5 cr in luggage </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 23 (bdnews24.com)  Customs officials at Zia International Airport on Wednesday held a man with a huge amount of foreign currencies, worth around Tk 5 crore, in his luggage. The arrestee, Mazharul Islam, was challenged on the boarding bridge, Shamsul Islam Khan, superintendent of the customs intelligence division, told bdnews24.com. He was scheduled to fly Dubai on an Emirates Airlines flight. When questioned, his replies were "scattered" and he eventually admitted he had foreign currencies in his luggage, Khan added. The luggage was brought out of the hold just before take off, searched and the currencies of several Middle-Eastern countries were recovered worth Tk 4,72,68,000. Preparation for a case is underway, Khan said. bd
